			      <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
				        <p>Cāntisirī — uterine sister of Great King 
					Siri-Cāntamūla, sacrificer of the Aśvamedha, giver of many
					times tens of millions of (pieces of) gold; wife of the
					Great Talavara Vāsiṭṭhīputta Kandasiri of the Pūkīyas, Great-Talavara-wife — in
					order to increase the lifespan and leading to victory after
					victory of her son-in-law, King Māṭharīputta
					Siri-Vīrapurisadatta of the Ikṣvākus ... and (for the sake of
					her own) well-being and happiness in both worlds and
						<foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">nirvāṇa</foreign> ...</p>
			      </div>
